ðŸ§± Basic HTML Document Structure

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>My First Web Page</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
    <p>This is my first HTML page.</p>
  </body>
</html>

ðŸ“– Explanation of Each Part:

<!DOCTYPE html> :	Declares that this is an HTML5 document (must be the first line).
<html> :	The root of the HTML document; all content goes inside this tag.
<head> : Contains metadata (data about the page), not shown on the page itself.
<meta charset="UTF-8"> : Tells the browser to use UTF-8 character encoding (supports all languages).
<title>	: Sets the title of the web page (shown on the browser tab).
<body> : Contains everything that is visible on the page â€” text, images, links, etc.
<h1> : Heading tag â€“ usually the main title of the page.
<p> :	Paragraph tag â€“ used for blocks of text.
